# Webs in the Dark

The gallery ahead is webbed floor to ceiling — old sheets of it, grey and heavy with dust. But the path through it is *swept*. Someone keeps this road open.

The drips go quiet first. Then the whisper of a bowstring taking weight. {{sfx:bolt}}

## Ambush

{{music:steel}} Shapes detach from the webs above you — lean, silent, skin like slate and eyes like coals. {{sfx:blades}} One of them speaks a word that eats the torchlight whole. {{sfx:darkness}}

> [!dm] Round 1: crossbows from elevation + *darkness* on the party's light source. They focus whoever carries the BOTTLE — they've been told to see what the surfacers found, not to kill. ⚑ If asked why: they answer to a priestess, and she answers to the Spider Queen.

## The Priestess

{{music:priestess}} From the webs at the far end, a taller figure watches the fight with her arms folded — and only steps in if her stalkers start losing. {{sfx:skitter}}

> [!dm] Her goal is INFORMATION. At half strength she calls the retreat — smoke, webs, gone — taking a report about the party toward the pool. Anything captured (a stalker, her regalia) is a thread to what Lolth wants when Eilistraee walks free ([[grill-queue]]).
